==English==

===Etymology===
From [[duck tape]] as it was found useful for taping ductwork.

===Usage note===
As the two terms are pronounced practically identically except in careful speech, either may be used.  Note, however, that ''Duck&reg; tape'' is a registered trade mark.

===Noun===

# A generally gray waterproof tape used for a great many purposes, including fastening duct work, and possessing nearly mythic status in American culture.  Seriously.
#: ''Son, it's time you learned to use the family duct tape.''

